    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="643"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Dayton</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. <hi rend="smallcaps">423.]</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 19, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatches, from No. 465 to No. 468, both
                    inclusive, are duly received.</p>
                <p>No. 466, enclosing the copy of a despatch from Mr. Lane, United States consul at
                    Vera Cruz, and the protest of José Wallace Smith, referred to therein, were
                    immediately communicated by me to Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys. These complaints, <pb
                        facs="0829" n="747" xml:id="pg_747"/> like that referred to in your No. 465,
                    (the imprisonment of Mr. Mansfield, our consul at Tabasco,) he said must he
                    referred by him to the French authorities in Mexico before he could give an
                    answer. But he assured me these matters should he promptly investigated. It
                    will, of course, be some considerable time before a report on these cases can be
                    received from Mexico.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. L. DAYTON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
